excerpt: Centuries-old, green-domed mosque named for a founder of Indian Islam, housing his tomb.
detail_description: The Malik Deenar Juma Masjid is a centuries-old mosque situated near a river and named after an Indian Islam founder whose tomb it houses. It has undergone recent renovations and now offers modern amenities such as spacious parking, food cafes, and toilets for visitors. Despite these changes, the historical appearance of the mosque has been altered. Nonetheless, visitors can still appreciate one of the oldest wooden-carved mosques that serve as a monument. The entrance gateway provides insights into its rich history and heritage.
name: Malik Deenar Juma Masjid Thalangara Kasaragod
address: FXPQ+2M4, Malik Deenar Nagar, Thalangara, Kasaragod, Kerala 671122, India

excerpt: Kasaragod is a municipal town and the administrative headquarters of the Kasaragod district in the state of Kerala, India. Established in 1966, Kasaragod was the first municipal town in the district. It is the northernmost district of Kerala and is also known as Sapta Bhasha Sangama Bhumi. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Kasaragod, located in the northernmost part of Kerala, India, is a municipal town and serves as the administrative headquarters of Kasaragod district. Established in 1966, it holds the distinction of being the first municipal town in the district. Known as Sapta Bhasha Sangama Bhumi, or land of seven languages, Kasaragod offers a rich cultural tapestry.
name: Kasaragod

detail_description: If you find yourself in the charming town of Kasaragod, make sure to stop by Viceroy Restaurant, a culinary gem that’s hard to miss. Renowned for its delectable non-vegetarian offerings, this eatery is particularly famous for its biryani dishes that are nothing short of extraordinary. From the aromatic chicken and mutton biryanis to the rich butter chicken and flavorful mutton rogan josh, every bite promises an unforgettable dining experience.
name: Viceroy Restaurant
address: City Tower Hotel,, M.G.Road, Kasaragod, Kerala 671121, India

name: Mugal Darbar
address: Old Bus Stand, near Mubarak Masjid, Kasaragod, Kerala 671121, India

detail_description: Sea View Park is a hidden gem located near Kasaragod railway station, just a few meters away from the second platform. The park offers a serene environment with seating arrangements along the walkways and beautiful sunset views. It was established in 1993 and underwent renovations in 2018, making it an ideal spot to relax and unwind. Visitors can also enjoy swings and sliders for kids while observing various bird species.
name: Sea View Park

excerpt: Small Hindu temple on a lake in a tranquil, scenic environment featuring a well-known crocodile.
detail_description: SRI ANANTHAPADMANABHA SWAMY TEMPLE is a serene and picturesque Hindu temple situated on a lake. It boasts of a renowned crocodile, Babiya, and is managed by welcoming priests who provide insights into its history. This temple's inclusive policy allows visitors from all walks of life to enjoy its tranquil surroundings. Highly recommended for those seeking a peaceful retreat in Kumbla.
name: Shree Ananthapadmanabha Swamy Lake Temple Ananthapuram Kasaragod
address: P. O, Via, Ananthapura, Kumbla (Kumble), Kerala 671321, India

excerpt: Centuries-old Hindu temple dedicated to gods Shiva & Ganesh, with carved scenes from the “Ramayana.”
detail_description: The Madhur Sri Madanantheshwara vinayaka Temple is an ancient Hindu temple located on the banks of River Madhuvahini in Kasaragod, Kerala. The temple was constructed by the Mypadi rulers in the 10th century and later renovated in the 15th century. It is dedicated to gods Shiva and Ganesh, with intricate wood carvings depicting scenes from the Ramayana.
name: Madhur Shree Madanantheshwara Siddi Vinayaka Temple

excerpt: Green hill with unpaved trekking trails to its summit, topped by a large boulder.
detail_description: Ranipuram, a hill station in Kasargod district of Kerala, is often referred to as the "ooty of kerala". Situated approximately 40 km from Kanhangad, it offers a picturesque landscape with green hills and unpaved trekking trails leading to its summit. The top is adorned with a large boulder, providing an amazing view of the surrounding area. It is an ideal destination for a weekend drive, offering breathtaking scenery and opportunities for capturing beautiful photographs.
name: Ranipuram

excerpt: Boxy hilltop fortress sited above the Chandragiri River offering dramatic sunset views.
detail_description: Situated atop a boxy hill, the Chandragiri Fort is an ancient 17th-century structure made of laterite stone. Perched on a hill, it offers breathtaking sunset vistas over the Chandragiri River, allowing visitors to enjoy panoramic views of Kasaragod harbour. Although the parking area and viewpoint are poorly maintained, this wheelchair-accessible site provides a serene atmosphere adorned with picturesque beauty. Visitors can capture stunning photographs without the need for entry tickets.
name: Chandragiri Fort

detail_description: The Hosdurg Fort, located in Kanhangad, is a massive structure that has the potential to become a popular tourist attraction if properly maintained. With its impressive size, visitors can enjoy panoramic views of the Arabian Sea and the nearby Manjampothikunnu hill. It is an ideal spot for relaxation in the evenings. Unfortunately, the fort currently lies in a state of disrepair, overgrown with grasses.
name: Hosdurg Fort
